name: 10,000,000 Volt Thunderbolt
flavor_text: The user, Pikachu wearing a cap, powers up a jolt of electricity using its Z-Power and unleashes it. Critical hits land more easily.

name: Absorb
flavor_text: A nutrient-draining attack. The user’s HP is restored by up to half the damage taken by the target.

name: Accelerock
flavor_text: The user smashes into the target at high speed. This move always goes first.

name: Acid
flavor_text: Opposing Pokémon are attacked with a spray of harsh acid. This may also lower their Sp. Def stats.

name: Acid Armor
flavor_text: The user alters its cellular structure to liquefy itself, sharply boosting its Defense stat.

name: Acid Spray
flavor_text: The user attacks by spitting fluid that works to melt the target. This also harshly lowers the target’s Sp. Def stat.

name: Acrobatics
flavor_text: The user nimbly strikes the target. This attack does massive damage if the user isn’t holding an item.

name: Acupressure
flavor_text: The user applies pressure to stress points, sharply boosting one of its or its allies’ stats.

name: Aerial Ace
flavor_text: The user confounds the target with speed, then slashes. This attack never misses.

name: Aeroblast
flavor_text: A vortex of air is shot at the target to inflict damage. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

name: After You
flavor_text: The user helps the target and makes it use its move right after the user.

name: Agility
flavor_text: The user relaxes and lightens its body to move faster. This sharply boosts its Speed stat.

name: Air Cutter
flavor_text: The user launches razor-like wind to slash opposing Pokémon. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

name: Air Slash
flavor_text: The user attacks with a blade of air that slices even the sky. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Ally Switch
flavor_text: The user teleports using a strange power and switches places with one of its allies. This move’s chance of failing rises if it is used in succession.

name: Amnesia
flavor_text: The user temporarily empties its mind to forget its concerns. This sharply boosts the user’s Sp. Def stat.

name: Anchor Shot
flavor_text: The user entangles the target with its anchor chain while attacking. The target becomes unable to flee.

name: Ancient Power
flavor_text: The user attacks with a prehistoric power. This may also boost all the user’s stats at once.

name: Apple Acid
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with an acidic liquid created from tart apples. This also lowers the target’s Sp. Def stat.

name: Aqua Cutter
flavor_text: The user expels pressurized water to cut at the target like a blade. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

name: Aqua Jet
flavor_text: The user lunges at the target to inflict damage, moving at blinding speed. This move always goes first.

name: Aqua Ring
flavor_text: The user envelops itself in a veil made of water. It regains some HP every turn.

name: Aqua Step
flavor_text: The user toys with the target and attacks it using light and fluid dance steps. This also boosts the user’s Speed stat.

name: Aqua Tail
flavor_text: The user attacks by swinging its tail as if it were a vicious wave in a raging storm.

name: Arm Thrust
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with open-palmed arm thrusts. This move hits two to five times in a row.

name: Armor Cannon
flavor_text: The user shoots its own armor out as blazing projectiles. This also lowers the user’s Defense and Sp. Def stats.

name: Aromatherapy
flavor_text: The user releases a soothing scent that heals all status conditions affecting the user’s party.

name: Aromatic Mist
flavor_text: The user boosts the Sp. Def stat of an ally Pokémon by using a mysterious aroma.

name: Assist
flavor_text: The user hurriedly and randomly uses a move among those known by ally Pokémon.

name: Assurance
flavor_text: This move’s power is doubled if the target has already taken some damage in the same turn.

name: Astonish
flavor_text: The user attacks the target by crying out in a startling fashion. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Astral Barrage
flavor_text: The user attacks by sending a frightful amount of small ghosts at opposing Pokémon.

name: Attack Order
flavor_text: The user calls out its underlings to pummel the target. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

name: Attract
flavor_text: If the target is of the opposite gender to the user, it becomes infatuated with the user and will sometimes be unable to use its moves.

name: Aura Sphere
flavor_text: The user lets loose a pulse of aura power from deep within its body at the target. This attack never misses.

name: Aura Wheel
flavor_text: Morpeko attacks and boosts its Speed stat with the energy stored in its cheeks. This move’s type changes depending on the user’s form.

name: Aurora Beam
flavor_text: The target is hit with a rainbow-colored beam. This may also lower the target’s Attack stat.

name: Aurora Veil
flavor_text: This move reduces damage from physical and special moves for five turns. This can be used only when it is snowing.

name: Autotomize
flavor_text: The user sheds part of its body to make itself lighter and sharply raise its Speed stat.

name: Avalanche
flavor_text: This move’s power is doubled if the target has inflicted damage on the user in the same turn.

name: Axe Kick
flavor_text: The user attacks by kicking up into the air and slamming its heel down upon the target. This may also confuse the target. If it misses, the user takes damage instead.

name: Baby-Doll Eyes
flavor_text: The user stares at the target with its baby-doll eyes, which lowers the target’s Attack stat. This move always goes first.

name: Baddy Bad
flavor_text: The user acts bad and attacks the target. A wondrous wall of light is put up to weaken the power of the opposing Pokémon’s physical moves.

name: Baneful Bunker
flavor_text: In addition to protecting the user from attacks, this move also poisons any attacker that makes direct contact.

name: Barb Barrage
flavor_text: The user launches countless toxic barbs to inflict damage. This may also poison the target. This move’s power is doubled if the target is already poisoned.

name: Barrage
flavor_text: Round objects are hurled at the target to strike two to five times in a row.

name: Barrier
flavor_text: The user throws up a sturdy wall that sharply raises its Defense stat.

name: Baton Pass
flavor_text: The user switches places with a party Pokémon in waiting and passes along any stat changes.

name: Beak Blast
flavor_text: The user first heats up its beak, and then it attacks the target. Making direct contact with the user while it’s heating up its beak results in a burn.

name: Beat Up
flavor_text: The user gets all party Pokémon to attack the target. The more party Pokémon, the greater the number of attacks.

name: Behemoth Bash
flavor_text: The user becomes a gigantic shield and slams into the target. This move inflicts twice the damage if the target is Dynamaxed.

name: Behemoth Blade
flavor_text: The user becomes a gigantic sword and cuts the target. This move inflicts twice the damage if the target is Dynamaxed.

name: Belch
flavor_text: The user lets out a damaging belch at the target. The user must eat a held Berry to use this move.

name: Belly Drum
flavor_text: The user maximizes its Attack stat but loses HP equal to half its max HP.

name: Bestow
flavor_text: The user passes its held item to the target when the target isn’t holding an item.

name: Bide
flavor_text: The user endures attacks for two turns, then strikes back to cause double the damage taken.

name: Bind
flavor_text: A long body, tentacles, or the like are used to bind and squeeze the target for four to five turns.

name: Bite
flavor_text: The target is bitten with viciously sharp fangs. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Bitter Blade
flavor_text: The user focuses its bitter feelings toward the world of the living into a slashing attack. The user’s HP is restored by up to half the damage taken by the target.

name: Bitter Malice
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with spine-chilling resentment. This also lowers the target’s Attack stat.

name: Blast Burn
flavor_text: The target is razed by a fiery explosion. The user can’t move on the next turn.

name: Blaze Kick
flavor_text: The user launches a kick that has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit. This may also leave the target with a burn.

name: Bleakwind Storm
flavor_text: The user attacks with savagely cold winds that cause both body and spirit to tremble. This may also lower the Speed stats of opposing Pokémon.

name: Blizzard
flavor_text: A howling blizzard is summoned to strike opposing Pokémon. This may also leave the opposing Pokémon frozen.

name: Block
flavor_text: The user blocks the target’s way with arms spread wide to prevent the target from fleeing.

name: Blood Moon
flavor_text: The user unleashes the full brunt of its spirit from a full moon that shines as red as blood. This move can't be used twice in a row.

name: Blue Flare
flavor_text: The user attacks by engulfing the target in an intense, yet beautiful, blue flame. This may also leave the target with a burn.

name: Body Press
flavor_text: The user attacks by slamming its body into the target. The higher the user’s Defense stat, the greater the damage this move deals.

name: Body Slam
flavor_text: The user attacks by dropping onto the target with its full body weight. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

name: Bolt Beak
flavor_text: The user stabs the target with its electrified beak. This move’s power is doubled if the user moves before the target.

name: Bolt Strike
flavor_text: The user surrounds itself with a great amount of electricity and charges the target. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

name: Bone Club
flavor_text: The user clubs the target with a bone. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Bone Rush
flavor_text: The user attacks by striking the target with a hard bone. This move hits two to five times in a row.

name: Bonemerang
flavor_text: The user throws the bone it holds. The bone loops around to damage the target twice—coming and going.

name: Boomburst
flavor_text: The user attacks everything around it with the destructive power of a terrible explosive sound.

name: Bounce
flavor_text: The user bounces up high on the first turn, then drops onto the target on the next turn. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

name: Bouncy Bubble
flavor_text: The user attacks by shooting water bubbles at the target. It then absorbs water and restores its HP by half the damage taken by the target.

name: Branch Poke
flavor_text: The user attacks the target by poking it with a sharply pointed branch.

name: Brave Bird
flavor_text: The user tucks in its wings and charges at a low altitude. This also damages the user quite a lot.

name: Breaking Swipe
flavor_text: The user swings its tough tail wildly and attacks opposing Pokémon. This also lowers their Attack stats.

name: Brick Break
flavor_text: The user attacks with a swift chop. This move can also break barriers, such as Light Screen and Reflect.

name: Brine
flavor_text: This move’s power is doubled if the target’s HP is at half or less.

name: Brutal Swing
flavor_text: The user swings its body around violently to inflict damage on everything in its vicinity.

name: Bubble
flavor_text: A spray of countless bubbles is jetted at the opposing Pokémon. This may also lower their Speed stat.

name: Bubble Beam
flavor_text: A spray of bubbles is forcefully ejected at the target. This may also lower the target’s Speed stat.

name: Bug Bite
flavor_text: The user attacks by biting the target. If the target is holding a Berry, the user eats it and gains its effect.

name: Bug Buzz
flavor_text: The user vibrates to generate a damaging sound wave. This may also lower the target’s Sp. Def stat.

name: Bulk Up
flavor_text: The user tenses its muscles to bulk up its body, boosting its Attack and Defense stats.

name: Bulldoze
flavor_text: The user strikes everything around it by stomping down on the ground. This lowers the Speed stats of those hit.

name: Bullet Punch
flavor_text: The user strikes the target with tough punches as fast as bullets. This move always goes first.

name: Bullet Seed
flavor_text: The user attacks by forcefully shooting seeds at the target. This move hits two to five times in a row.

name: Burn Up
flavor_text: To inflict massive damage, the user burns itself out. After using this move, the user will no longer be Fire type.

name: Burning Jealousy
flavor_text: The user attacks with energy from jealousy. This leaves all opposing Pokémon that have had their stats boosted during the turn with a burn.

name: Buzzy Buzz
flavor_text: The user shoots a jolt of electricity to attack the target. This also leaves the target with paralysis.

name: Calm Mind
flavor_text: The user quietly focuses its mind and calms its spirit to boost its Sp. Atk and Sp. Def stats.

name: Camouflage
flavor_text: The user’s type is changed depending on its environment, such as at water’s edge, in grass, or in a cave.

name: Captivate
flavor_text: If any opposing Pokémon is the opposite gender of the user, it is charmed, which harshly lowers its Sp. Atk stat.

name: Catastropika
flavor_text: The user, Pikachu, surrounds itself with the maximum amount of electricity using its Z-Power and pounces on its target with full force.

name: Ceaseless Edge
flavor_text: The user slashes its shell blade at the target, aiming to land a critical hit. Shell splinters left behind by this attack remain scattered under the target as spikes.

name: Celebrate
flavor_text: The Pokémon congratulates you on your special day!

name: Charge
flavor_text: The user becomes charged, boosting the power of the next Electric-type move it uses. This also boosts the user’s Sp. Def stat.

name: Charge Beam
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with an electric charge. The residual electricity may also boost the user’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Charm
flavor_text: The user gazes at the target rather charmingly, making it less wary. This harshly lowers the target’s Attack stat.

name: Chatter
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with sound waves of deafening chatter. This also confuses the target.

name: Chilling Water
flavor_text: The user attacks the target by showering it with water that’s so cold it saps the target’s power. This also lowers the target’s Attack stat.

name: Chilly Reception
flavor_text: The user tells a chillingly bad joke before switching places with a party Pokémon in waiting. This summons a snowstorm lasting five turns.

name: Chip Away
flavor_text: Looking for an opening, the user strikes consistently. The target’s stat changes don’t affect this attack’s damage.

name: Chloroblast
flavor_text: The user launches its amassed chlorophyll to inflict damage on the target. This also damages the user.

name: Circle Throw
flavor_text: The target is thrown, and a different Pokémon is dragged out. In the wild, this ends a battle against a single Pokémon.

name: Clamp
flavor_text: The target is clamped and squeezed by the user’s very thick and sturdy shell for four to five turns.

name: Clanging Scales
flavor_text: The user rubs the scales on its entire body and makes a huge noise to attack opposing Pokémon. The user’s Defense stat is lowered after the attack.

name: Clangorous Soul
flavor_text: The user boosts all its stats by using some of its own HP.

name: Clangorous Soulblaze
flavor_text: After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Kommo-o, attacks the opposing Pokémon with full force. This move boosts the user’s stats.

name: Clear Smog
flavor_text: The user attacks the target by throwing a clump of special mud. All stat changes are eliminated.

name: Close Combat
flavor_text: The user fights the target up close, inflicting damage without guarding itself. This also lowers the user’s Defense and Sp. Def stats.

name: Coaching
flavor_text: The user properly coaches its ally Pokémon, boosting their Attack and Defense stats.

name: Coil
flavor_text: The user coils up and concentrates. This boosts its Attack and Defense stats as well as its accuracy.

name: Collision Course
flavor_text: The user transforms and crashes to the ground, causing a massive prehistoric explosion. This move’s power is boosted more than usual if it’s a supereffective hit.

name: Comet Punch
flavor_text: The target is hit with a flurry of punches that strike two to five times in a row.

name: Comeuppance
flavor_text: The user retaliates with much greater force against the opponent that last inflicted damage on it.

name: Confide
flavor_text: The user tells the target a secret, and the target loses its ability to concentrate. This lowers the target’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Confuse Ray
flavor_text: The target is exposed to a sinister ray that causes confusion.

name: Confusion
flavor_text: The target is hit with a weak telekinetic force to inflict damage. This may also confuse the target.

name: Constrict
flavor_text: The target is attacked with long, creeping tentacles, vines, or the like. This may also lower the target’s Speed stat.

name: Conversion
flavor_text: The user changes its type to become the same type as the move at the top of the list of moves it knows.

name: Conversion 2
flavor_text: The user changes its type to make itself resistant to the type of the move the target used last.

name: Copycat
flavor_text: The user mimics the move used immediately before it. This move fails if no other move has been used yet.

name: Core Enforcer
flavor_text: If the Pokémon damaged by this move have already used their moves that turn, this move eliminates the effects of those Pokémon’s Abilities.

name: Corrosive Gas
flavor_text: The user surrounds everything around it with highly acidic gas and melts away items held by other Pokémon.

name: Cosmic Power
flavor_text: The user absorbs a mystical power from space to boost its Defense and Sp. Def stats.

name: Cotton Guard
flavor_text: The user protects itself by wrapping its body in soft cotton, drastically boosting its Defense stat.

name: Cotton Spore
flavor_text: The user releases cotton-like spores that cling to opposing Pokémon. This harshly lowers their Speed stats.

name: Counter
flavor_text: A retaliatory attack that counters any physical move, inflicting double the damage taken.

name: Court Change
flavor_text: With its mysterious power, the user swaps the effects on either side of the field.

name: Covet
flavor_text: The user endearingly approaches the target, then steals the target’s held item.

name: Crabhammer
flavor_text: The target is hammered with a large pincer. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

name: Crafty Shield
flavor_text: The user protects itself and its allies from status moves with a mysterious power. This does not stop moves that do damage.

name: Cross Chop
flavor_text: The user delivers a double chop with its forearms crossed. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

name: Cross Poison
flavor_text: A slashing attack with a poisonous blade that may also poison the target. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

name: Crunch
flavor_text: The user crunches up the target with sharp fangs. This may also lower the target’s Defense stat.

name: Crush Claw
flavor_text: The user slashes the target with hard and sharp claws. This may also lower the target’s Defense stat.

name: Crush Grip
flavor_text: The target is crushed with great force. The more HP the target has left, the greater the move’s power.

name: Curse
flavor_text: A move that has different effects depending on whether the user is a Ghost type or not.

name: Cut
flavor_text: The target is cut with a scythe, a claw, or the like to inflict damage.

name: Dark Pulse
flavor_text: The user releases a horrible aura imbued with ill intent. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Dark Void
flavor_text: Opposing Pokémon are dragged into a world of total darkness that puts them to sleep.

name: Darkest Lariat
flavor_text: The user swings both arms and hits the target. The target’s stat changes don’t affect the damage inflicted by this move.

name: Dazzling Gleam
flavor_text: The user damages opposing Pokémon by emitting a powerful flash.

name: Decorate
flavor_text: The user sharply boosts the target’s Attack and Sp. Atk stats by decorating the target.

name: Defend Order
flavor_text: The user calls out its underlings to shield its body, boosting its Defense and Sp. Def stats.

name: Defense Curl
flavor_text: The user curls up and boosts its Defense stat.

name: Defog
flavor_text: A strong wind blows away the target’s barriers such as Reflect or Light Screen. This also lowers the target’s evasiveness.

name: Destiny Bond
flavor_text: If the user is knocked out after using this move, the Pokémon that knocked it out will also faint. This move’s chance of failing rises if it is used in succession.

name: Detect
flavor_text: This move enables the user to protect itself from all attacks. Its chance of failing rises if it is used in succession.

name: Diamond Storm
flavor_text: The user whips up a storm of diamonds to damage opposing Pokémon. This may also sharply boost the user’s Defense stat.

name: Dig
flavor_text: The user burrows into the ground on the first turn, then attacks on the next turn.

name: Dire Claw
flavor_text: The user lashes out at the target with ruinous claws, aiming to land a critical hit. This may also leave the target poisoned, paralyzed, or asleep.

name: Disable
flavor_text: For four turns, the target will be unable to use whichever move it last used.

name: Disarming Voice
flavor_text: Letting out a charming cry, the user does emotional damage to opposing Pokémon. This attack never misses.

name: Discharge
flavor_text: The user strikes everything around it by letting loose a flare of electricity. This may also leave those hit by the attack with paralysis.

name: Dive
flavor_text: The user dives on the first turn, then floats up and attacks on the next turn.

name: Dizzy Punch
flavor_text: The target is hit with rhythmically launched punches. This may also leave the target confused.

name: Doodle
flavor_text: The user captures the very essence of the target in a sketch. This changes the Abilities of the user and its ally Pokémon to that of the target.

name: Doom Desire
flavor_text: Two turns after this move is used, a concentrated bundle of light blasts the target.

name: Double Hit
flavor_text: The user slams the target with a tail or the like. The target is hit twice in a row.

name: Double Iron Bash
flavor_text: The user uses the hex nut in its chest as an axis to spin, striking the target with its arms twice in a row. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Double Kick
flavor_text: The user attacks by kicking the target twice in a row using two feet.

name: Double Shock
flavor_text: The user discharges all the electricity from its body to perform a high-damage attack. After using this move, the user will no longer be Electric type.

name: Double Slap
flavor_text: The target is slapped repeatedly, back and forth, two to five times in a row.

name: Double Team
flavor_text: By moving rapidly, the user makes illusory copies of itself to boost its evasiveness.

name: Double-Edge
flavor_text: A reckless life-risking tackle in which the user rushes the target. This also damages the user quite a lot.

name: Draco Meteor
flavor_text: Comets are summoned down from the sky onto the target. The recoil from this move harshly lowers the user’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Dragon Ascent
flavor_text: The user attacks the target by dropping out of the sky at high speed. This also lowers the user’s Defense and Sp. Def stats.

name: Dragon Breath
flavor_text: The user exhales a mighty gust that inflicts damage. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

name: Dragon Claw
flavor_text: The user slashes the target with huge, sharp claws to inflict damage.

name: Dragon Dance
flavor_text: The user vigorously performs a mystic, powerful dance that boosts its Attack and Speed stats.

name: Dragon Darts
flavor_text: The user attacks twice using Dreepy. If there are two opposing Pokémon, this move hits each of them once.

name: Dragon Energy
flavor_text: Converting its life-force into power, the user attacks opposing Pokémon. The lower the user’s HP, the lower the move’s power.

name: Dragon Hammer
flavor_text: The user uses its body like a hammer to attack the target and inflict damage.

name: Dragon Pulse
flavor_text: The target is attacked with a shock wave generated by the user’s gaping mouth.

name: Dragon Rage
flavor_text: This attack hits the target with a shock wave of pure rage. This attack always inflicts 40 HP damage.

name: Dragon Rush
flavor_text: The user tackles the target while exhibiting overwhelming menace. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Dragon Tail
flavor_text: The target is knocked away, and a different Pokémon is dragged out. In the wild, this ends a battle against a single Pokémon.

name: Drain Punch
flavor_text: The user attacks with an energy-draining punch. The user’s HP is restored by up to half the damage taken by the target.

name: Draining Kiss
flavor_text: The user steals the target’s HP with a kiss. The user’s HP is restored by over half the damage taken by the target.

name: Dream Eater
flavor_text: The user eats the dreams of a sleeping target. The user’s HP is restored by up to half the damage taken by the target.

name: Drill Peck
flavor_text: A corkscrewing attack that strikes the target with a sharp beak acting as a drill.

name: Drill Run
flavor_text: The user crashes into the target while rotating its body like a drill. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

name: Drum Beating
flavor_text: The user plays its drum, controlling the drum’s roots to attack the target. This also lowers the target’s Speed stat.

name: Dual Chop
flavor_text: The user attacks its target by hitting it with brutal strikes. The target is hit twice in a row.

name: Dual Wingbeat
flavor_text: The user slams the target with its wings to inflict damage. The target is hit twice in a row.

name: Dynamax Cannon
flavor_text: The user condenses energy within its body and unleashes that energy from its core to inflict damage.

name: Dynamic Punch
flavor_text: The user attacks by punching the target with full concentrated power. This also confuses the target.

name: Earth Power
flavor_text: The user makes the ground under the target erupt with power. This may also lower the target’s Sp. Def stat.

name: Earthquake
flavor_text: The user sets off an earthquake that strikes every Pokémon around it.

name: Echoed Voice
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with an echoing voice. If this move is used consecutively by any Pokémon, its power is boosted.

name: Eerie Impulse
flavor_text: The user’s body generates an eerie impulse. Exposing the target to it harshly lowers the target’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Eerie Spell
flavor_text: The user attacks with its tremendous psychic power. This also drains 3 PP from the move last used by the target.

name: Egg Bomb
flavor_text: A large egg is hurled at the target with maximum force to inflict damage.

name: Electric Terrain
flavor_text: The user turns the ground into Electric Terrain for five turns, powering up Electric-type moves. Pokémon on the ground can no longer fall asleep.

name: Electrify
flavor_text: If the target is electrified before it uses a move, the target’s move becomes Electric type for that turn.

name: Electro Ball
flavor_text: The user hurls an electric orb at the target. The faster the user is than the target, the greater the move’s power.

name: Electro Drift
flavor_text: The user races forward at ultrafast speeds, piercing its target with futuristic electricity. This move’s power is boosted more than usual if it’s a supereffective hit.

name: Electroweb
flavor_text: The user captures opposing Pokémon in an electric net to inflict damage. This also lowers their Speed stats.

name: Embargo
flavor_text: This move prevents the target from using its held item for five turns. Its Trainer is also prevented from using items on it.

name: Ember
flavor_text: The target is attacked with small flames. This may also leave the target with a burn.

name: Encore
flavor_text: The user compels the target to keep using the move it encored for three turns.

name: Endeavor
flavor_text: The user inflicts damage by cutting down the target’s HP to roughly equal the user’s HP.

name: Endure
flavor_text: The user endures any attack with at least 1 HP. This move’s chance of failing rises if used in succession.

name: Energy Ball
flavor_text: The user draws power from nature and fires it at the target. This may also lower the target’s Sp. Def stat.

name: Entrainment
flavor_text: The user dances with an odd rhythm that compels the target to mimic it, making the target’s Ability the same as the user’s.

name: Eruption
flavor_text: The user attacks opposing Pokémon with explosive fury. The lower the user’s HP, the lower the move’s power.

name: Esper Wing
flavor_text: The user slashes the target with aura-enriched wings. This also boosts the user’s Speed stat. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

name: Eternabeam
flavor_text: This is Eternatus’s most powerful attack in its original form. The user can’t move on the next turn.

name: Expanding Force
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with its psychic power. When the ground is Psychic Terrain, this move’s power is boosted and it damages all opposing Pokémon.

name: Explosion
flavor_text: The user attacks everything around it by causing a tremendous explosion. The user faints upon using this move.

name: Extrasensory
flavor_text: The user attacks with an odd, unseeable power. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Extreme Evoboost
flavor_text: After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Eevee, gets energy from its evolved friends and boosts its stats sharply.

name: Extreme Speed
flavor_text: The user charges the target at blinding speed. This move always goes first.

name: Facade
flavor_text: This move’s power is doubled if the user is poisoned, burned, or paralyzed.

name: Fairy Lock
flavor_text: By locking down the battlefield, the user keeps all Pokémon from fleeing during the next turn.

name: Fairy Wind
flavor_text: The user attacks by stirring up a fairy wind to strike the target.

name: Fake Out
flavor_text: This attack hits first and makes the target flinch. It works only on the first turn each time the user enters battle.

name: Fake Tears
flavor_text: The user feigns crying to fluster the target. This harshly lowers the target’s Sp. Def stat.

name: False Surrender
flavor_text: The user pretends to bow its head, but then it stabs the target with its disheveled hair. This attack never misses.

name: False Swipe
flavor_text: A restrained attack that prevents the target from fainting. The target is left with at least 1 HP.

name: Feather Dance
flavor_text: The user covers the target’s body with a mass of down that harshly lowers its Attack stat.

name: Feint
flavor_text: This attack can hit a target using a move such as Protect or Detect. This also lifts the effects of those moves.

name: Feint Attack
flavor_text: The user approaches the target disarmingly, then throws a sucker punch. This attack never misses.

name: Fell Stinger
flavor_text: When the user knocks out a target with this move, the user’s Attack stat is boosted drastically.

name: Fiery Dance
flavor_text: Cloaked in flames, the user attacks the target by dancing and flapping its wings. This may also boost the user’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Fiery Wrath
flavor_text: The user transforms its wrath into a fire-like aura to attack. This may also make opposing Pokémon flinch.

name: Fillet Away
flavor_text: The user sharply boosts its Attack, Sp. Atk, and Speed stats by using its own HP.

name: Final Gambit
flavor_text: The user risks everything to attack the target. The user faints but inflicts damage equal to its own HP.

name: Fire Blast
flavor_text: The target is attacked with an intense blast of all-consuming fire. This may also leave the target with a burn.

name: Fire Fang
flavor_text: The user bites with flame-cloaked fangs. This may also make the target flinch or leave it with a burn.

name: Fire Lash
flavor_text: The user strikes the target with a burning lash. This also lowers the target’s Defense stat.

name: Fire Pledge
flavor_text: A column of fire hits the target. When used with its grass counterpart, this move’s power is boosted and a vast sea of fire appears.

name: Fire Punch
flavor_text: The target is attacked with a fiery punch. This may also leave the target with a burn.

name: Fire Spin
flavor_text: The user traps the target inside a fierce vortex of fire that inflicts damage for four to five turns.

name: First Impression
flavor_text: Although this move has great power, it works only on the first turn each time the user enters battle.

name: Fishious Rend
flavor_text: The user rends the target with its hard gills. This move’s power is doubled if the user moves before the target.

name: Fissure
flavor_text: The user opens up a fissure in the ground and drops the target in. The target faints instantly if this attack hits.

name: Flail
flavor_text: The user flails about aimlessly to attack. The less HP the user has, the greater the move’s power.

name: Flame Burst
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with a bursting flame. The bursting flame damages Pokémon next to the target as well.

name: Flame Charge
flavor_text: Cloaking itself in flame, the user attacks the target. Then, building up momentum, the user boosts its Speed stat.

name: Flame Wheel
flavor_text: The user attacks by cloaking itself in fire and charging at the target. This may also leave the target with a burn.

name: Flamethrower
flavor_text: The target is scorched with an intense blast of fire. This may also leave the target with a burn.

name: Flare Blitz
flavor_text: The user cloaks itself in fire and charges the target to inflict damage. This also damages the user quite a lot and may leave the target with a burn.

name: Flash
flavor_text: The user flashes a light that lowers the target’s accuracy. It can also be used to illuminate caves.

name: Flash Cannon
flavor_text: The user gathers all its light energy and releases it at once. This may also lower the target’s Sp. Def stat.

name: Flatter
flavor_text: Flattery is used to confuse the target. However, this also boosts the target’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Fleur Cannon
flavor_text: The user unleashes a strong beam. The recoil from this move harshly lowers the user’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Fling
flavor_text: The user flings its held item at the target to attack. This move’s power and effects depend on the item.

name: Flip Turn
flavor_text: After making its attack, the user rushes back to switch places with a party Pokémon in waiting.

name: Floaty Fall
flavor_text: The user floats in the air, and then dives at a steep angle to attack the target. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Floral Healing
flavor_text: The user restores the target’s HP by up to half its max HP. More HP is restored when the ground is Grassy Terrain.

name: Flower Shield
flavor_text: The user raises the Defense stats of all Grass-type Pokémon in battle with a mysterious power.

name: Flower Trick
flavor_text: The user throws a rigged bouquet of flowers at the target. This attack never misses and always lands a critical hit.

name: Fly
flavor_text: The user flies up into the sky on the first turn, then attacks on the next turn.

name: Flying Press
flavor_text: The user dives down onto the target from the sky. This move is Fighting and Flying type simultaneously.

name: Focus Blast
flavor_text: The user heightens its mental focus and unleashes its power. This may also lower the target’s Sp. Def stat.

name: Focus Energy
flavor_text: The user takes a deep breath and focuses so that its future attacks have a heightened chance of landing critical hits.

name: Focus Punch
flavor_text: The user focuses its mind before launching a punch. This move fails if the user is hit before using the move.

name: Follow Me
flavor_text: The user draws attention to itself, making all opposing Pokémon take aim only at the user.

name: Force Palm
flavor_text: The target is attacked with a shock wave. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

name: Foresight
flavor_text: Enables a Ghost-type target to be hit by Normal- and Fighting-type attacks. This also enables an evasive target to be hit.

name: Forest's Curse
flavor_text: The user puts a forest curse on the target. This adds Grass type to the target’s type.

name: Foul Play
flavor_text: The user turns the target’s strength against it. The higher the target’s Attack stat, the greater the damage this move inflicts.

name: Freeze Shock
flavor_text: The turn after using this move, the user hits the target with electrically charged ice to inflict damage. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

name: Freeze-Dry
flavor_text: The user rapidly cools the target. This may also leave the target frozen. This move is super effective on Water types.

name: Freezing Glare
flavor_text: The user shoots its psychic power from its eyes to attack. This may also leave the target frozen.

name: Freezy Frost
flavor_text: The user attacks with a crystal made of cold frozen haze. It eliminates every stat change among all the Pokémon engaged in battle.

name: Frenzy Plant
flavor_text: The user slams the target with the roots of an enormous tree. The user can’t move on the next turn.

name: Frost Breath
flavor_text: The user attacks by blowing its cold breath on the target. This move always lands a critical hit.

name: Frustration
flavor_text: This full-power attack grows more powerful the less the user likes its Trainer.

name: Fury Attack
flavor_text: The user attacks by jabbing the target with a horn, a beak, or the like. This move hits two to five times in a row.

name: Fury Cutter
flavor_text: The user attacks by slashing the target with scythes, claws, or the like. This attack becomes more powerful if it hits in succession.

name: Fury Swipes
flavor_text: The user attacks by raking the target with claws, scythes, or the like. This move hits two to five times in a row.

name: Fusion Bolt
flavor_text: The user throws down a giant lightning bolt. This move’s power is boosted when influenced by an enormous flame.

name: Fusion Flare
flavor_text: The user brings down a giant flame. This move’s power is boosted when influenced by an enormous lightning bolt.

name: Future Sight
flavor_text: Two turns after this move is used, a hunk of psychic energy attacks the target.

name: Gastro Acid
flavor_text: The user hurls up its stomach acids on the target. The fluid eliminates the effect of the target’s Ability.

name: Gear Grind
flavor_text: The user attacks by throwing steel gears at the target twice in a row.

name: Gear Up
flavor_text: The user engages its gears to raise the Attack and Sp. Atk stats of ally Pokémon with the Plus or Minus Ability.

name: Genesis Supernova
flavor_text: After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Mew, attacks the target with full force. The terrain will be charged with psychic energy.

name: Geomancy
flavor_text: The user absorbs energy on the first turn, then sharply boosts its Sp. Atk, Sp. Def, and Speed stats on the next turn.

name: Giga Drain
flavor_text: A nutrient-draining attack. The user’s HP is restored by up to half the damage taken by the target.

name: Giga Impact
flavor_text: The user charges at the target using every bit of its power. The user can’t move on the next turn.

name: Gigaton Hammer
flavor_text: The user swings its whole body around to attack with its huge hammer. This move can’t be used twice in a row.

name: Glacial Lance
flavor_text: The user attacks by hurling a blizzard-cloaked icicle lance at opposing Pokémon.

name: Glaciate
flavor_text: The user attacks by blowing freezing cold air at opposing Pokémon. This also lowers their Speed stats.

name: Glaive Rush
flavor_text: The user throws its entire body into a reckless charge. Attacks from opposing Pokémon during the next turn cannot miss and will inflict double damage.

name: Glare
flavor_text: The user intimidates the target with the pattern on its belly to cause paralysis.

name: Glitzy Glow
flavor_text: The user bombards the target with telekinetic force. A wondrous wall of light is put up to weaken the power of the opposing Pokémon’s special moves.

name: Grass Knot
flavor_text: The user snares the target with grass and trips it. The heavier the target, the greater the move’s power.

name: Grass Pledge
flavor_text: A column of grass hits the target. When used with its water counterpart, this move’s power is boosted and a vast swamp appears.

name: Grass Whistle
flavor_text: The user plays a pleasant melody that lulls the target into a deep sleep.

name: Grassy Glide
flavor_text: Gliding on the ground, the user attacks the target. This move always goes first on Grassy Terrain.

name: Grassy Terrain
flavor_text: The user turns the ground into Grassy Terrain for five turns. This restores the HP of Pokémon on the ground a little every turn and powers up Grass-type moves.

name: Grav Apple
flavor_text: The user inflicts damage by dropping an apple from high above. This also lowers the target’s Defense stat.

name: Gravity
flavor_text: Enables Flying types or Pokémon with the Levitate Ability to be hit by Ground-type moves for five turns. Moves that involve flying can’t be used.

name: Growl
flavor_text: The user growls in an endearing way, making opposing Pokémon less wary. This lowers their Attack stats.

name: Growth
flavor_text: The user’s body grows all at once, boosting the Attack and Sp. Atk stats.

name: Grudge
flavor_text: If the user faints, the user’s grudge fully depletes the PP of the opponent’s move that knocked it out.

name: Guard Split
flavor_text: The user employs its psychic power to average its Defense and Sp. Def stats with those of the target.

name: Guard Swap
flavor_text: The user employs its psychic power to switch changes to its Defense and Sp. Def stats with the target.

name: Guardian of Alola
flavor_text: The user, the Land Spirit Pokémon, obtains Alola’s energy using its Z-Power and attacks the target with full force. This reduces the target’s HP greatly.

name: Guillotine
flavor_text: A vicious tearing attack with big pincers. The target faints instantly if this attack hits.

name: Gunk Shot
flavor_text: The user shoots filthy garbage at the target to attack. This may also poison the target.

name: Gust
flavor_text: A gust of wind is whipped up by wings and launched at the target to inflict damage.

name: Gyro Ball
flavor_text: The user tackles the target with a high-speed spin. The slower the user is than the target, the greater the move’s power.

name: Hail
flavor_text: The user summons a hailstorm lasting five turns. It damages all Pokémon except Ice types.

name: Hammer Arm
flavor_text: The user swings its strong, heavy fist at the target to inflict damage. This also lowers the user’s Speed stat.

name: Happy Hour
flavor_text: Using Happy Hour doubles the amount of prize money received after battle.

name: Harden
flavor_text: The user stiffens all the muscles in its body to boost its Defense stat.

name: Haze
flavor_text: The user creates a haze that eliminates every stat change among all the Pokémon engaged in battle.

name: Head Charge
flavor_text: The user charges its head into the target, using its powerful guard hair. This also damages the user a little.

name: Head Smash
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with a hazardous full-power headbutt. This also damages the user terribly.

name: Headbutt
flavor_text: The user sticks out its head and attacks by charging straight into the target. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Headlong Rush
flavor_text: The user smashes into the target in a full-body tackle. This also lowers the user’s Defense and Sp. Def stats.

name: Heal Bell
flavor_text: The user makes a soothing bell chime to cure the status conditions of all its fellow party Pokémon and allies.

name: Heal Block
flavor_text: For five turns, the user prevents the opposing team from using any moves, Abilities, or held items that recover HP.

name: Heal Order
flavor_text: The user calls out its underlings to heal it. The user regains up to half of its max HP.

name: Heal Pulse
flavor_text: The user emits a healing pulse that restores the target’s HP by up to half its max HP.

name: Healing Wish
flavor_text: The user faints. In return, the Pokémon taking its place will have its HP restored and status conditions cured.

name: Heart Stamp
flavor_text: The user unleashes a vicious blow after its cute act makes the target less wary. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Heart Swap
flavor_text: The user employs its psychic power to switch stat changes with the target.

name: Heat Crash
flavor_text: The user slams into the target with its flame-covered body. The more the user outweighs the target, the greater the move’s power.

name: Heat Wave
flavor_text: The user attacks by exhaling hot breath on opposing Pokémon. This may also leave them with a burn.

name: Heavy Slam
flavor_text: The user slams into the target with its heavy body. The more the user outweighs the target, the greater the move’s power.

name: Helping Hand
flavor_text: The user assists an ally by boosting the power of that ally’s attack.

name: Hex
flavor_text: This relentless attack does massive damage to a target affected by status conditions.

name: Hidden Power
flavor_text: A unique attack that varies in type depending on the Pokémon using it.

name: High Horsepower
flavor_text: The user fiercely attacks the target using its entire body.

name: High Jump Kick
flavor_text: The target is attacked with a knee kick from a jump. If this move misses, the user takes damage instead.

name: Hold Back
flavor_text: The user holds back when it attacks, and the target is left with at least 1 HP.

name: Hold Hands
flavor_text: The user and an ally hold hands. This makes them very happy.

name: Hone Claws
flavor_text: The user sharpens its claws to boost its Attack stat and accuracy.

name: Horn Attack
flavor_text: The target is jabbed with a sharply pointed horn to inflict damage.

name: Horn Drill
flavor_text: The user stabs the target with a horn that rotates like a drill. The target faints instantly if this attack hits.

name: Horn Leech
flavor_text: The user drains the target’s energy with its horns. The user’s HP is restored by up to half the damage taken by the target.

name: Howl
flavor_text: The user howls loudly to rouse itself and its allies. This boosts their Attack stats.

name: Hurricane
flavor_text: The user attacks by wrapping the target in a fierce wind. This may also confuse the target.

name: Hydro Cannon
flavor_text: The target is hit with a watery blast. The user can’t move on the next turn.

name: Hydro Pump
flavor_text: The target is blasted by a huge volume of water launched under great pressure.

name: Hydro Steam
flavor_text: Power increases in harsh sunlight.

name: Hyper Beam
flavor_text: The target is attacked with a powerful beam. The user can’t move on the next turn.

name: Hyper Drill
flavor_text: The user spins the pointed part of its body at high speed to pierce the target. This attack can hit a target using a move such as Protect or Detect.

name: Hyper Fang
flavor_text: The user bites hard on the target with its sharp front fangs. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Hyper Voice
flavor_text: The user attacks by letting loose a horribly loud, resounding cry.

name: Hyperspace Fury
flavor_text: Using its many arms, the user unleashes a barrage of attacks that ignore the effects of moves like Protect and Detect. This also lowers the user’s Defense stat.

name: Hyperspace Hole
flavor_text: Using a hyperspace hole, the user appears right next to the target and strikes. This attack can hit a target using a move such as Protect or Detect.

name: Hypnosis
flavor_text: The user employs hypnotic suggestion to make the target fall asleep.

name: Ice Ball
flavor_text: The user attacks the target for five turns. The move’s power increases each time it hits.

name: Ice Beam
flavor_text: The target is struck with an icy-cold beam of energy. This may also leave the target frozen.

name: Ice Burn
flavor_text: The turn after using this move, the user surrounds the target with an ultracold, freezing wind to inflict damage. This may also leave the target with a burn.

name: Ice Fang
flavor_text: The user bites with cold-infused fangs. This may also make the target flinch or leave it frozen.

name: Ice Hammer
flavor_text: The user swings its strong, heavy fist at the target to inflict damage. This also lowers the user’s Speed stat.

name: Ice Punch
flavor_text: The target is attacked with an icy punch. This may also leave the target frozen.

name: Ice Shard
flavor_text: The user flash-freezes chunks of ice and hurls them at the target. This move always goes first.

name: Ice Spinner
flavor_text: The user covers its feet in thin ice and twirls around, slamming into the target. This move’s spinning motion also destroys the terrain.

name: Icicle Crash
flavor_text: The user attacks by crashing large icicles onto the target. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Icicle Spear
flavor_text: The user attacks by launching sharp icicles at the target. This move hits two to five times in a row.

name: Icy Wind
flavor_text: The user attacks with a gust of chilled air. This also lowers opposing Pokémon’s Speed stats.

name: Imprison
flavor_text: If opposing Pokémon know any move also known by the user, they are prevented from using it.

name: Incinerate
flavor_text: The user attacks opposing Pokémon with fire. If a Pokémon is holding a certain item, such as a Berry, the item becomes burned up and unusable.

name: Infernal Parade
flavor_text: The user attacks with myriad fireballs. This may also leave the target with a burn. This move’s power is doubled if the target has a status condition.

name: Inferno
flavor_text: The user attacks by engulfing the target in an intense fire. This leaves the target with a burn.

name: Infestation
flavor_text: The target is infested and attacked for four to five turns. The target can’t flee during this time.

name: Ingrain
flavor_text: The user lays roots that restore its own HP every turn. Because the user is now rooted, it can’t switch out.

name: Instruct
flavor_text: The user instructs the target to reuse the move last used by the target.

name: Ion Deluge
flavor_text: The user disperses electrically charged particles, which changes Normal-type moves to Electric-type moves.

name: Iron Defense
flavor_text: The user hardens its body’s surface like iron, sharply boosting its Defense stat.

name: Iron Head
flavor_text: The user slams the target with its steel-hard head. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Iron Tail
flavor_text: The target is slammed with a steel-hard tail. This may also lower the target’s Defense stat.

name: Ivy Cudgel
flavor_text: The user strikes with an ivy-wrapped cudgel. This move's type changes depending on the mask worn by the user, and it has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

name: Jaw Lock
flavor_text: This move prevents the user and the target from switching out until either of them faints. The effect goes away if either of the Pokémon leaves the field.

name: Jet Punch
flavor_text: The user summons a torrent around its fist and punches at blinding speed. This move always goes first.

name: Judgment
flavor_text: The user releases countless shots of light at the target. This move’s type changes depending on the kind of plate held by the user.

name: Jump Kick
flavor_text: The user jumps up high, then strikes with a kick. If the kick misses, the user hurts itself.

name: Jungle Healing
flavor_text: The user becomes one with the jungle, restoring HP and curing status conditions for itself and its ally Pokémon currently in the battle.

name: Karate Chop
flavor_text: The target is attacked with a sharp chop. Critical hits land more easily.

name: Kinesis
flavor_text: The user distracts the target by bending a spoon. This lowers the target’s accuracy.

name: King's Shield
flavor_text: The user takes a defensive stance while it protects itself from damage. This also lowers the Attack stat of any attacker that makes direct contact.

name: Knock Off
flavor_text: The user slaps down the target’s held item, making it unusable for that battle. This move does more damage if the target has a held item.

name: Kowtow Cleave
flavor_text: The user slashes at the target after kowtowing to make the target let down its guard. This attack never misses.

name: Land's Wrath
flavor_text: The user gathers the energy of the land and focuses that power on opposing Pokémon to inflict damage.

name: Laser Focus
flavor_text: The user concentrates intensely. The attack on the next turn always results in a critical hit.

name: Lash Out
flavor_text: The user lashes out to vent its frustration toward the target. This move’s power is doubled if the user’s stats were lowered during this turn.

name: Last Resort
flavor_text: This move can be used only after the user has used all the other moves it knows in the battle.

name: Last Respects
flavor_text: The user attacks to avenge its allies. The more defeated allies there are in the user’s party, the greater the move’s power.

name: Lava Plume
flavor_text: The user torches everything around it in an inferno of scarlet flames. This may also leave those it hits with a burn.

name: Leaf Blade
flavor_text: The user handles a sharp leaf like a sword and cuts the target to inflict damage. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

name: Leaf Storm
flavor_text: The user whips up a storm of leaves around the target. The recoil from this move harshly lowers the user’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Leaf Tornado
flavor_text: The user attacks its target by encircling it in sharp leaves. This attack may also lower the target’s accuracy.

name: Leafage
flavor_text: The user attacks by pelting the target with leaves.

name: Leech Life
flavor_text: The user drains the target’s blood. The user’s HP is restored by up to half the damage taken by the target.

name: Leech Seed
flavor_text: A seed is planted on the target. It steals some HP from the target every turn.

name: Leer
flavor_text: The user gives opposing Pokémon an intimidating leer that lowers their Defense stats.

name: Let's Snuggle Forever
flavor_text: After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Mimikyu, punches the target with full force.

name: Lick
flavor_text: The user licks the target with a long tongue to inflict damage. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

name: Life Dew
flavor_text: The user scatters mysterious water around and restores the HP of itself and its ally Pokémon currently in the battle.

name: Light Screen
flavor_text: A wondrous wall of light is put up to reduce damage from special moves for five turns.

name: Light That Burns the Sky
flavor_text: This attack inflicts Attack or Sp. Atk damage— whichever stat is higher for the user, Necrozma. This move ignores the target’s Ability.

name: Light of Ruin
flavor_text: Drawing power from the Eternal Flower, the user fires a powerful beam of light. This also damages the user terribly.

name: Liquidation
flavor_text: The user slams into the target using a full-force blast of water. This may also lower the target’s Defense stat.

name: Lock-On
flavor_text: The user takes sure aim at the target. This ensures the user’s next move does not miss that target.

name: Lovely Kiss
flavor_text: With a scary face, the user tries to kiss the target. If it succeeds, the target falls asleep.

name: Low Kick
flavor_text: A powerful low kick that makes the target fall over. The heavier the target, the greater the move’s power.

name: Low Sweep
flavor_text: The user makes a swift attack on the target’s legs, which lowers the target’s Speed stat.

name: Lucky Chant
flavor_text: The user chants an incantation toward the sky, preventing opposing Pokémon from landing critical hits for five turns.

name: Lumina Crash
flavor_text: The user attacks by unleashing a peculiar light that even affects the mind. This also harshly lowers the target’s Sp. Def stat.

name: Lunar Blessing
flavor_text: The user receives a blessing from the crescent moon, restoring HP and curing status conditions for itself and its ally Pokémon currently in the battle.

name: Lunar Dance
flavor_text: The user faints. In return, the Pokémon taking its place will have its HP and PP restored and its status conditions cured.

name: Lunge
flavor_text: The user makes a lunge at the target, attacking with full force. This also lowers the target’s Attack stat.

name: Luster Purge
flavor_text: The user lets loose a damaging burst of light. This may also lower the target’s Sp. Def stat.

name: Mach Punch
flavor_text: The user throws a punch at blinding speed. This move always goes first.

name: Magic Coat
flavor_text: Moves like Leech Seed and moves that inflict status conditions are blocked by a barrier and reflected back to the user of those moves.

name: Magic Powder
flavor_text: The user scatters a cloud of magic powder that changes the target’s type to Psychic.

name: Magic Room
flavor_text: The user creates a bizarre area in which Pokémon’s held items lose their effects for five turns.

name: Magical Leaf
flavor_text: The user scatters curious leaves that chase the target. This attack never misses.

name: Magma Storm
flavor_text: The user traps the target inside a maelstrom of fire that inflicts damage for four to five turns.

name: Magnet Bomb
flavor_text: The user launches steel bombs that stick to the target. This attack never misses.

name: Magnet Rise
flavor_text: The user levitates using electrically generated magnetism for five turns.

name: Magnetic Flux
flavor_text: The user manipulates magnetic fields, which boosts the Defense and Sp. Def stats of ally Pokémon with the Plus Ability or the Minus Ability.

name: Magnitude
flavor_text: The user attacks everything around it with a ground-shaking quake. Its power varies.

name: Make It Rain
flavor_text: The user attacks by throwing out a mass of coins. This also lowers the user’s Sp. Atk stat. Money is earned after the battle.

name: Malicious Moonsault
flavor_text: The user, Incineroar, strengthens its body using its Z-Power and crashes into the target with full force.

name: Mat Block
flavor_text: Using a pulled-up mat as a shield, the user protects itself and its allies from damaging moves. This does not stop status moves.

name: Matcha Gotcha
flavor_text: The user fires a blast of tea that it mixed. The user's HP is restored by up to half the damage taken by the target. This may also leave the target with a burn.

name: Me First
flavor_text: The user cuts ahead of the target to copy and use the target’s intended move with greater power. This move fails if it isn’t used first.

name: Mean Look
flavor_text: The user pins the target with a dark, arresting look. The target becomes unable to flee.

name: Meditate
flavor_text: The user meditates to awaken the power deep within its body and raise its Attack stat.

name: Mega Drain
flavor_text: A nutrient-draining attack. The user’s HP is restored by up to half the damage taken by the target.

name: Mega Kick
flavor_text: The target is attacked by a kick launched with muscle-packed power.

name: Mega Punch
flavor_text: The target is slugged by a punch thrown with muscle-packed power.

name: Megahorn
flavor_text: Using its tough and impressive horn, the user rams into the target with no letup.

name: Memento
flavor_text: The user faints. In return, the target’s Attack and Sp. Atk stats are harshly lowered.

name: Menacing Moonraze Maelstrom
flavor_text: After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Lunala, attacks the target with full force. This move can ignore the effect of the target’s Ability.

name: Metal Burst
flavor_text: The user retaliates with much greater force against the opponent that last inflicted damage on it.

name: Metal Claw
flavor_text: The target is raked with steel claws. This may also boost the user’s Attack stat.

name: Metal Sound
flavor_text: A horrible sound like scraping metal harshly lowers the target’s Sp. Def stat.

name: Meteor Assault
flavor_text: The user attacks wildly with its thick leek. The user can’t move on the next turn, because the force of this move makes it stagger.

name: Meteor Beam
flavor_text: The user gathers energy from space and boosts its Sp. Atk stat on the first turn, then attacks on the next turn.

name: Meteor Mash
flavor_text: The target is hit with a hard punch fired like a meteor. This may also boost the user’s Attack stat.

name: Metronome
flavor_text: The user waggles a finger and stimulates its brain into randomly using nearly any move.

name: Milk Drink
flavor_text: The user restores its own HP by up to half its max HP.

name: Mimic
flavor_text: The user copies the move last used by the target. The copied move can be used until the user of Mimic leaves the battle.

name: Mind Blown
flavor_text: The user attacks everything around it by causing its own head to explode. This also damages the user.

name: Mind Reader
flavor_text: The user senses the target’s movements with its mind to ensure its next attack does not miss the target.

name: Minimize
flavor_text: The user compresses its body to make itself look smaller, which sharply boosts its evasiveness.

name: Miracle Eye
flavor_text: Enables a Dark-type target to be hit by Psychic-type attacks. This also enables an evasive target to be hit.

name: Mirror Coat
flavor_text: A retaliatory attack that counters any special move, inflicting double the damage taken.

name: Mirror Move
flavor_text: The user counters the target by mimicking the target’s last move.

name: Mirror Shot
flavor_text: The user lets loose a flash of energy at the target from its polished body. This may also lower the target’s accuracy.

name: Mist
flavor_text: The user cloaks itself and its allies in a white mist that prevents any of their stats from being lowered for five turns.

name: Mist Ball
flavor_text: A mist-like flurry of down envelops and damages the target. This may also lower the target’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Misty Explosion
flavor_text: The user attacks everything around it and faints upon using this move. This move’s power is boosted on Misty Terrain.

name: Misty Terrain
flavor_text: This protects Pokémon on the ground from status conditions and halves damage from Dragon-type moves for five turns.

name: Moonblast
flavor_text: Borrowing the power of the moon, the user attacks the target. This may also lower the target’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Moongeist Beam
flavor_text: The user emits a sinister ray to attack the target. This move can be used on the target regardless of its Ability.

name: Moonlight
flavor_text: The user restores its own HP. The amount of HP regained varies with the weather.

name: Morning Sun
flavor_text: The user restores its own HP. The amount of HP regained varies with the weather.

name: Mortal Spin
flavor_text: The user performs a spin attack that can also eliminate the effects of such moves as Bind, Wrap, and Leech Seed. This also poisons opposing Pokémon.

name: Mountain Gale
flavor_text: The user hurls giant chunks of ice at the target to inflict damage. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Mud Bomb
flavor_text: The user launches a hard-packed mud ball to attack. This may also lower the target’s accuracy.

name: Mud Shot
flavor_text: The user attacks by hurling a blob of mud at the target. This also lowers the target’s Speed stat.

name: Mud Sport
flavor_text: The user kicks up mud on the battlefield. This weakens Electric-type moves for five turns.

name: Mud-Slap
flavor_text: The user hurls mud in the target’s face to inflict damage and lower its accuracy.

name: Muddy Water
flavor_text: The user attacks by shooting muddy water at opposing Pokémon. This may also lower their accuracy.

name: Multi-Attack
flavor_text: Cloaking itself in powerful energy, the user slams into the target to inflict damage. This move’s type changes depending on the kind of memory disc held by the user.

name: Mystical Fire
flavor_text: The user attacks by breathing a special, hot fire. This also lowers the target’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Mystical Power
flavor_text: The user attacks by emitting a mysterious power. This also boosts the user’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Nasty Plot
flavor_text: The user stimulates its brain by thinking bad thoughts. This sharply boosts the user’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Natural Gift
flavor_text: The user draws power to attack by using its held Berry. The Berry determines the move’s type and power.

name: Nature Power
flavor_text: This attack makes use of nature’s power. Its effects vary depending on the user’s environment.

name: Nature's Madness
flavor_text: The user hits the target with the full wrath of nature. This cuts the target’s HP in half.

name: Needle Arm
flavor_text: The user attacks by wildly swinging its thorny arms. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Night Daze
flavor_text: The user looses a pitch-black shock wave at the target to inflict damage. This may also lower the target’s accuracy.

name: Night Shade
flavor_text: The user makes the target see a frightening mirage. It inflicts damage equal to the user’s level.

name: Night Slash
flavor_text: The user slashes the target the instant an opportunity arises. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

name: Nightmare
flavor_text: A sleeping target sees a nightmare that inflicts some damage every turn.

name: No Retreat
flavor_text: This move boosts all the user’s stats but prevents the user from switching out or fleeing.

name: Noble Roar
flavor_text: Letting out a noble roar, the user intimidates the target and lowers the target’s Attack and Sp. Atk stats.

name: Nuzzle
flavor_text: The user attacks by nuzzling its electrified cheeks against the target. This also leaves the target with paralysis.

name: Oblivion Wing
flavor_text: The user absorbs the target’s HP. The user’s HP is restored by over half the damage taken by the target.

name: Obstruct
flavor_text: This move enables the user to protect itself from all attacks. Its chance of failing rises if used in succession. Direct contact harshly lowers the attacker’s Defense stat.

name: Oceanic Operetta
flavor_text: The user, Primarina, summons a massive amount of water using its Z-Power and attacks the target with full force.

name: Octazooka
flavor_text: The user attacks by spraying ink in the target’s face. This may also lower the target’s accuracy.

name: Octolock
flavor_text: The user locks the target in and prevents it from fleeing. This move also lowers the target’s Defense and Sp. Def every turn.

name: Odor Sleuth
flavor_text: Enables a Ghost-type target to be hit by Normal- and Fighting-type attacks. This also enables an evasive target to be hit.

name: Ominous Wind
flavor_text: The user blasts the target with a gust of repulsive wind. This may also raise all the user’s stats at once.

name: Order Up
flavor_text: The user attacks with elegant poise. If the user has a Tatsugiri in its mouth, this move boosts one of the user’s stats based on the Tatsugiri’s form.

name: Origin Pulse
flavor_text: The user attacks opposing Pokémon with countless beams of light that glow a deep and brilliant blue.

name: Outrage
flavor_text: The user rampages and attacks for two to three turns. The user then becomes confused.

name: Overdrive
flavor_text: The user attacks opposing Pokémon by twanging a guitar or bass guitar, causing a huge echo and strong vibration.

name: Overheat
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with all its might. The recoil from this move harshly lowers the user’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Pain Split
flavor_text: The user adds its HP to the target’s HP, then equally splits the combined HP between the target and itself.

name: Parabolic Charge
flavor_text: The user attacks everything around it. The user’s HP is restored by half the damage taken by those hit.

name: Parting Shot
flavor_text: With a parting threat, the user lowers the target’s Attack and Sp. Atk stats. Then it switches places with a party Pokémon in waiting.

name: Pay Day
flavor_text: Coins are hurled at the target to inflict damage. Money is earned after the battle.

name: Payback
flavor_text: The user stores power, then attacks. This move’s power is doubled if the user moves after the target.

name: Peck
flavor_text: The target is jabbed with a sharply pointed beak or horn to inflict damage.

name: Perish Song
flavor_text: Any Pokémon that hears this song faints in three turns, unless it switches out of battle.

name: Petal Blizzard
flavor_text: The user stirs up a violent petal blizzard and damages everything around it.

name: Petal Dance
flavor_text: The user attacks the target by scattering petals for two to three turns. The user then becomes confused.

name: Phantom Force
flavor_text: The user vanishes somewhere, then strikes the target on the next turn. This move hits even if the target protects itself.

name: Photon Geyser
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with a pillar of light. This move inflicts damage using the Attack or Sp. Atk stat— whichever is higher for the user.

name: Pika Papow
flavor_text: The more Pikachu loves its Trainer, the greater the move’s power. It never misses.

name: Pin Missile
flavor_text: The user attacks by shooting sharp spikes at the target. This move hits two to five times in a row.

name: Plasma Fists
flavor_text: The user attacks with electrically charged fists. This move changes Normal-type moves to Electric-type moves.

name: Play Nice
flavor_text: The user and the target become friends, and the target loses its will to fight. This lowers the target’s Attack stat.

name: Play Rough
flavor_text: The user attacks by playing rough with the target. This may also lower the target’s Attack stat.

name: Pluck
flavor_text: The user attacks by pecking the target. If the target is holding a Berry, the user eats it and gains its effect.

name: Poison Fang
flavor_text: The user bites the target with toxic fangs. This may also leave the target badly poisoned.

name: Poison Gas
flavor_text: A cloud of poison gas is sprayed in the faces of opposing Pokémon, poisoning those it hits.

name: Poison Jab
flavor_text: The target is stabbed with a tentacle, an arm, or the like steeped in poison. This may also poison the target.

name: Poison Powder
flavor_text: The user scatters a cloud of poisonous dust that poisons the target.

name: Poison Sting
flavor_text: The user stabs the target with a poisonous stinger to inflict damage. This may also poison the target.

name: Poison Tail
flavor_text: The user hits the target with its tail. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit and may also poison the target.

name: Pollen Puff
flavor_text: The user attacks the enemy with a pollen puff that explodes. If the target is an ally, it gives the ally a pollen puff that restores its HP instead.

name: Poltergeist
flavor_text: The user attacks by controlling the target’s item. This move fails if the target isn’t holding an item.

name: Population Bomb
flavor_text: The user’s fellows gather in droves to perform a combo attack that hits the target one to ten times in a row.

name: Pounce
flavor_text: The user attacks by pouncing on the target. This also lowers the target’s Speed stat.

name: Pound
flavor_text: The target is physically pounded with a long tail, a foreleg, or the like.

name: Powder
flavor_text: The user covers the target in a combustible powder. If the target uses a Fire-type move, the powder explodes and damages the target.

name: Powder Snow
flavor_text: The user attacks with a chilling gust of powdery snow. This may also leave opposing Pokémon frozen.

name: Power Gem
flavor_text: The user attacks with a ray of light that sparkles as if it were made of gemstones.

name: Power Shift
flavor_text: The user swaps its Attack and Defense stats.

name: Power Split
flavor_text: The user employs its psychic power to average its Attack and Sp. Atk stats with those of the target.

name: Power Swap
flavor_text: The user employs its psychic power to switch changes to its Attack and Sp. Atk stats with the target.

name: Power Trick
flavor_text: The user employs its psychic power to switch its Attack stat with its Defense stat.

name: Power Trip
flavor_text: The user boasts its strength and attacks the target. The more the user’s stats are boosted, the greater the move’s power.

name: Power Whip
flavor_text: The user violently whirls its vines, tentacles, or the like to lash the target.

name: Power-Up Punch
flavor_text: Striking opponents over and over makes the user’s fists harder. Hitting a target raises the Attack stat.

name: Precipice Blades
flavor_text: The user attacks opposing Pokémon by manifesting the power of the land in fearsome blades of stone.

name: Present
flavor_text: The user attacks by giving the target a gift with a hidden trap. The gift restores HP sometimes, however.

name: Prismatic Laser
flavor_text: The user shoots powerful lasers using the power of a prism. The user can’t move on the next turn.

name: Protect
flavor_text: This move enables the user to protect itself from all attacks. Its chance of failing rises if it is used in succession.

name: Psybeam
flavor_text: The target is attacked with a peculiar ray. This may also confuse the target.

name: Psyblade
flavor_text: Power increases on Electric Terrain.

name: Psych Up
flavor_text: The user hypnotizes itself into copying any stat change made by the target.

name: Psychic
flavor_text: The target is hit with a strong telekinetic force to inflict damage. This may also lower the target’s Sp. Def stat.

name: Psychic Fangs
flavor_text: The user attacks by biting the target with its psychic capabilities. This move can also break barriers, such as Light Screen and Reflect.

name: Psychic Terrain
flavor_text: This protects Pokémon on the ground from priority moves and powers up Psychic-type moves for five turns.

name: Psycho Boost
flavor_text: The user attacks the target at full power. The attack’s recoil harshly lowers the user’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Psycho Cut
flavor_text: The user tears at the target with blades formed by psychic power. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

name: Psycho Shift
flavor_text: Using its psychic power of suggestion, the user transfers its status conditions to the target.

name: Psyshield Bash
flavor_text: Cloaking itself in psychic energy, the user slams into the target. This also boosts the user’s Defense stat.

name: Psyshock
flavor_text: The user materializes an odd psychic wave to attack the target. This move deals physical damage.

name: Psystrike
flavor_text: The user materializes an odd psychic wave to attack the target. This move deals physical damage.

name: Psywave
flavor_text: The target is attacked with an odd psychic wave. The attack varies in intensity.

name: Pulverizing Pancake
flavor_text: Z-Power brings out the true capabilities of the user, Snorlax. The Pokémon moves its enormous body energetically and attacks the target with full force.

name: Punishment
flavor_text: The more the target has powered up with stat changes, the greater the move’s power.

name: Purify
flavor_text: The user cures the target’s status condition. If the move succeeds, it also restores the user’s own HP.

name: Pursuit
flavor_text: The power of this attack move is doubled if it’s used on a target that’s switching out of battle.

name: Pyro Ball
flavor_text: The user attacks by igniting a small stone and launching it as a fiery ball at the target. This may also leave the target with a burn.

name: Quash
flavor_text: The user suppresses the target and makes its move go last.

name: Quick Attack
flavor_text: The user lunges at the target to inflict damage, moving at blinding speed. This move always goes first.

name: Quick Guard
flavor_text: The user protects itself and its allies from priority moves.

name: Quiver Dance
flavor_text: The user lightly performs a beautiful, mystic dance. This boosts the user’s Sp. Atk, Sp. Def, and Speed stats.

name: Rage
flavor_text: As long as this move is in use, the power of rage raises the Attack stat each time the user is hit in battle.

name: Rage Fist
flavor_text: The user converts its rage into energy to attack. The more times the user has been hit by attacks, the greater the move’s power.

name: Rage Powder
flavor_text: The user scatters a cloud of irritating powder to draw attention to itself. Opposing Pokémon aim only at the user.

name: Raging Bull
flavor_text: The user performs a tackle like a raging bull. This move’s type depends on the user’s form. It can also break barriers, such as Light Screen and Reflect.

name: Raging Fury
flavor_text: The user rampages around spewing flames for two to three turns. The user then becomes confused.

name: Rain Dance
flavor_text: The user summons a heavy rain that falls for five turns, powering up Water-type attacks. The rain also lowers the power of Fire-type attacks.

name: Rapid Spin
flavor_text: The user performs a spin attack that can also eliminate the effects of such moves as Bind, Wrap, and Leech Seed. This also boosts the user’s Speed stat.

name: Razor Leaf
flavor_text: Sharp-edged leaves are launched to slash at opposing Pokémon. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

name: Razor Shell
flavor_text: The user cuts the target with sharp shells to inflict damage. This may also lower the target’s Defense stat.

name: Razor Wind
flavor_text: In this two-turn attack, blades of wind hit opposing Pokémon on the second turn. Critical hits land more easily.

name: Recover
flavor_text: The user regenerates its cells, restoring its own HP by up to half its max HP.

name: Recycle
flavor_text: The user recycles a held item that has been used in battle so it can be used again.

name: Reflect
flavor_text: A wondrous wall of light is put up to reduce damage from physical moves for five turns.

name: Reflect Type
flavor_text: The user reflects the target’s type to become the same type as the target.

name: Refresh
flavor_text: The user rests to cure itself of poisoning, a burn, or paralysis.

name: Relic Song
flavor_text: The user sings an ancient song and attacks by appealing to the hearts of the listening opposing Pokémon. This may also induce sleep.

name: Rest
flavor_text: The user goes to sleep for two turns. This fully restores the user’s HP and cures any status conditions.

name: Retaliate
flavor_text: The user takes revenge for a fainted ally. This move’s power is boosted if an ally fainted in the previous turn.

name: Return
flavor_text: This full-power attack grows more powerful the more the user likes its Trainer.

name: Revelation Dance
flavor_text: The user attacks the target by dancing with all its might. This move becomes the same type as the user’s type.

name: Revenge
flavor_text: This attack move’s power is doubled if the user has been hurt by the opponent in the same turn.

name: Reversal
flavor_text: An all-out attack that becomes more powerful the less HP the user has.

name: Revival Blessing
flavor_text: The user bestows a loving blessing, reviving a party Pokémon that has fainted and restoring half that Pokémon’s max HP.

name: Rising Voltage
