flavor_text: The user attacks with electricity rising from the ground. This move’s power is doubled if the target is on Electric Terrain.

name: Roar
flavor_text: The target is scared off, and a different Pokémon is dragged out. In the wild, this ends a battle against a single Pokémon.

name: Roar of Time
flavor_text: The user blasts the target with power that distorts even time. The user can’t move on the next turn.

name: Rock Blast
flavor_text: The user attacks by hurling hard rocks at the target. This move hits two to five times in a row.

name: Rock Climb
flavor_text: A charging attack that may also leave the foe confused. It’s also one of the Pokétch’s hidden moves.

name: Rock Polish
flavor_text: The user polishes its body to reduce drag. This sharply boosts the user’s Speed stat.

name: Rock Slide
flavor_text: Large boulders are hurled at opposing Pokémon to inflict damage. This may also make the opposing Pokémon flinch.

name: Rock Smash
flavor_text: The user attacks with a punch. This may also lower the target’s Defense stat.

name: Rock Throw
flavor_text: The user picks up and throws a small rock at the target to inflict damage.

name: Rock Tomb
flavor_text: The user hurls boulders at the target to inflict damage. This also lowers the target’s Speed stat by cutting off its movement.

name: Rock Wrecker
flavor_text: The user launches a huge boulder at the target to attack. The user can’t move on the next turn.

name: Role Play
flavor_text: The user mimics the target completely, copying the target’s Ability.

name: Rolling Kick
flavor_text: The user lashes out with a quick, spinning kick. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Rollout
flavor_text: The user continually rolls into the target over five turns. This attack becomes more powerful each time it hits.

name: Roost
flavor_text: The user lands and rests its body. This move restores the user’s HP by up to half its max HP.

name: Rototiller
flavor_text: Tilling the soil, the user makes it easier for plants to grow. This raises the Attack and Sp. Atk stats of Grass-type Pokémon.

name: Round
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with a song. If others use this move, they will act immediately after the initial user, and the power of their Rounds will be boosted.

name: Ruination
flavor_text: The user summons a ruinous disaster. This cuts the target’s HP in half.

name: Sacred Fire
flavor_text: The target is razed with a mystical fire of great intensity. This may also leave the target with a burn.

name: Sacred Sword
flavor_text: The user attacks by slicing with a sword. The target’s stat changes don’t affect the damage inflicted by this move.

name: Safeguard
flavor_text: The user creates a protective field that prevents status conditions for five turns.

name: Salt Cure
flavor_text: The user salt cures the target, inflicting damage every turn. Steel and Water types are more strongly affected by this move.

name: Sand Attack
flavor_text: Sand is hurled in the target’s face, lowering the target’s accuracy.

name: Sand Tomb
flavor_text: The user traps the target inside a harshly raging sandstorm that inflicts damage for four to five turns.

name: Sandsear Storm
flavor_text: The user attacks by wrapping opposing Pokémon in fierce winds and searingly hot sand. This may also leave them with a burn.

name: Sandstorm
flavor_text: A five-turn sandstorm is summoned to damage all Pokémon except Rock, Ground, and Steel types. The sandstorm also boosts the Sp. Def stats of Rock types.

name: Sappy Seed
flavor_text: The user grows a gigantic stalk that scatters seeds to attack the target. The seeds drain the target’s HP every turn.

name: Scald
flavor_text: The user attacks by shooting boiling hot water at the target. This may also leave the target with a burn.

name: Scale Shot
flavor_text: The user attacks by shooting scales two to five times in a row. This move boosts the user’s Speed stat but lowers its Defense stat.

name: Scary Face
flavor_text: The user frightens the target with a scary face to harshly lower its Speed stat.

name: Scorching Sands
flavor_text: The user throws scorching sand at the target to attack. This may also leave the target with a burn.

name: Scratch
flavor_text: Hard, pointed, sharp claws rake the target to inflict damage.

name: Screech
flavor_text: An earsplitting screech harshly lowers the target’s Defense stat.

name: Searing Shot
flavor_text: The user torches everything around it in an inferno of scarlet flames. This may also leave those it hits with a burn.

name: Searing Sunraze Smash
flavor_text: After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Solgaleo, attacks the target with full force. This move can ignore the effect of the target’s Ability.

name: Secret Power
flavor_text: The additional effects of this attack depend upon where it was used.

name: Secret Sword
flavor_text: The user cuts with its long horn. The odd power contained in the horn deals physical damage to the target.

name: Seed Bomb
flavor_text: The user attacks by slamming a barrage of hard-shelled seeds down on the target from above.

name: Seed Flare
flavor_text: The user emits a shock wave from its body to attack the target. This may also harshly lower the target’s Sp. Def stat.

name: Seismic Toss
flavor_text: The target is thrown using the power of gravity. It inflicts damage equal to the user’s level.

name: Self-Destruct
flavor_text: The user attacks everything around it by causing an explosion. The user faints upon using this move.

name: Shadow Ball
flavor_text: The user attacks by hurling a shadowy blob at the target. This may also lower the target’s Sp. Def stat.

name: Shadow Bone
flavor_text: The user attacks by beating the target with a bone that contains a spirit. This may also lower the target’s Defense stat.

name: Shadow Claw
flavor_text: The user attacks by slashing the target with a sharp claw made from shadows. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

name: Shadow Force
flavor_text: The user disappears on the first turn, then attacks on the next turn. This move hits even if the target protects itself.

name: Shadow Punch
flavor_text: The user throws a punch from the shadows. This attack never misses.

name: Shadow Sneak
flavor_text: The user extends its shadow and attacks the target from behind. This move always goes first.

name: Sharpen
flavor_text: The user makes its edges more jagged, which raises its Attack stat.

name: Shed Tail
flavor_text: The user creates a substitute for itself using its own HP before switching places with a party Pokémon in waiting.

name: Sheer Cold
flavor_text: The target faints instantly. This move is less likely to hit the target if used by Pokémon other than Ice types.

name: Shell Side Arm
flavor_text: This move is either physical or special—whichever will inflict more damage. This may also poison the target.

name: Shell Smash
flavor_text: The user breaks its shell, which lowers its Defense and Sp. Def stats but sharply boosts its Attack, Sp. Atk, and Speed stats.

name: Shell Trap
flavor_text: The user sets a shell trap. If the user is hit by a physical move, the trap will explode and inflict damage on opposing Pokémon.

name: Shelter
flavor_text: The user makes its skin as hard as an iron shield, sharply boosting its Defense stat.

name: Shift Gear
flavor_text: The user rotates its gears, boosting its Attack stat and sharply boosting its Speed stat.

name: Shock Wave
flavor_text: The user strikes the target with a quick jolt of electricity. This attack never misses.

name: Shore Up
flavor_text: The user restores its own HP by up to half its max HP. It regains more HP in a sandstorm.

name: Signal Beam
flavor_text: The user attacks with a sinister beam of light. This may also confuse the target.

name: Silk Trap
flavor_text: The user spins a silken trap, protecting itself from damage while lowering the Speed stat of any attacker that makes direct contact.

name: Silver Wind
flavor_text: The target is attacked with powdery scales blown by the wind. This may also raise all the user’s stats.

name: Simple Beam
flavor_text: The user emits a mysterious psychic wave that changes the target’s Ability to Simple.

name: Sing
flavor_text: A soothing lullaby is sung in a beautiful voice that puts the target to sleep.

name: Sinister Arrow Raid
flavor_text: The user, Decidueye, creates countless arrows using its Z-Power and shoots the target with full force.

name: Sizzly Slide
flavor_text: The user cloaks itself in fire and charges at the target. This also leaves the target with a burn.

name: Sketch
flavor_text: This move enables the user to permanently learn the move last used by the target. Once used, Sketch disappears.

name: Skill Swap
flavor_text: The user employs its psychic power to exchange Abilities with the target.

name: Skitter Smack
flavor_text: The user skitters behind the target to attack. This also lowers the target’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Skull Bash
flavor_text: The user tucks in its head to raise its Defense stat on the first turn, then rams the target on the next turn.

name: Sky Attack
flavor_text: The user attacks the turn after using this move. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit and may also make the target flinch.

name: Sky Drop
flavor_text: The user takes the target into the sky, then drops it during the next turn. The target cannot attack while in the sky.

name: Sky Uppercut
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with an uppercut thrown skyward with force.

name: Slack Off
flavor_text: The user slacks off, restoring its own HP by up to half its max HP.

name: Slam
flavor_text: The target is slammed with a long tail, vines, or the like to inflict damage.

name: Slash
flavor_text: The target is attacked with a slash of claws, scythes, or the like. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

name: Sleep Powder
flavor_text: The user scatters a cloud of soporific dust that puts the target to sleep.

name: Sleep Talk
flavor_text: The user randomly uses one of the moves it knows. This move can only be used while the user is asleep.

name: Sludge
flavor_text: The user hurls unsanitary sludge at the target to inflict damage. This may also poison the target.

name: Sludge Bomb
flavor_text: The user hurls unsanitary sludge at the target to inflict damage. This may also poison the target.

name: Sludge Wave
flavor_text: The user strikes everything around it by swamping the area with a giant sludge wave. This may also poison those it hits.

name: Smack Down
flavor_text: The user throws a stone or similar projectile to attack the target. If the target is in the air, it will be knocked down to the ground.

name: Smart Strike
flavor_text: The user stabs the target with a sharp horn. This attack never misses.

name: Smelling Salts
flavor_text: This attack’s power is doubled when used on a target with paralysis. This also cures the target’s paralysis, however.

name: Smog
flavor_text: The target is attacked with a discharge of filthy gases. This may also poison the target.

name: Smokescreen
flavor_text: The user releases an obscuring cloud of smoke or ink. This lowers the target’s accuracy.

name: Snap Trap
flavor_text: The user snares the target in a snap trap that inflicts damage for four to five turns.

name: Snarl
flavor_text: The user yells as if it’s ranting about something, which lowers the Sp. Atk stats of opposing Pokémon.

name: Snatch
flavor_text: The user steals the effects of any attempts to use a healing or stat-changing move.

name: Snipe Shot
flavor_text: The user ignores the effects of opposing Pokémon’s moves and Abilities that draw in moves, allowing this move to hit the chosen target.

name: Snore
flavor_text: This attack can be used only if the user is asleep. The harsh noise may also make the target flinch.

name: Snowscape
flavor_text: The user summons a snowstorm lasting five turns. This boosts the Defense stats of Ice types.

name: Soak
flavor_text: The user shoots a torrent of water that changes the target’s type to Water.

name: Soft-Boiled
flavor_text: The user restores its own HP by up to half its max HP.

name: Solar Beam
flavor_text: The user gathers light on the first turn, then blasts a bundled beam on the next turn.

name: Solar Blade
flavor_text: The user gathers light on the first turn, then fills a blade with the light’s energy and attacks on the next turn.

name: Sonic Boom
flavor_text: The target is hit with a destructive shock wave that always inflicts 20 HP damage.

name: Soul-Stealing 7-Star Strike
flavor_text: After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Marshadow, punches and kicks the target consecutively with full force.

name: Spacial Rend
flavor_text: The user tears the target along with the space around it. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

name: Spark
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with an electrically charged tackle. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

name: Sparkling Aria
flavor_text: The user bursts into song, emitting many bubbles. Any Pokémon suffering from a burn will be cured by the touch of these bubbles.

name: Sparkly Swirl
flavor_text: The user attacks the target by wrapping it with a whirlwind of an overpowering scent. This also heals all status conditions of the user’s party.

name: Spectral Thief
flavor_text: The user hides in the target’s shadow, steals the target’s stat boosts, and then attacks.

name: Speed Swap
flavor_text: The user exchanges Speed stats with the target.

name: Spicy Extract
flavor_text: The user emits an incredibly spicy extract, sharply boosting the target’s Attack stat and harshly lowering the target’s Defense stat.

name: Spider Web
flavor_text: The user ensnares the target with thin, gooey silk so it can’t flee from battle.

name: Spike Cannon
flavor_text: Sharp spikes are shot at the target in rapid succession. They hit two to five times in a row.

name: Spikes
flavor_text: The user lays a trap of spikes at the feet of the opposing team. The spikes will damage opposing Pokémon that switch into battle.

name: Spiky Shield
flavor_text: In addition to protecting the user from attacks, this move also damages any attacker that makes direct contact.

name: Spin Out
flavor_text: The user spins furiously by straining its legs, inflicting damage on the target. This also harshly lowers the user’s Speed stat.

name: Spirit Break
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with so much force that it could break the target’s spirit. This also lowers the target’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Spirit Shackle
flavor_text: The user attacks while simultaneously stitching the target’s shadow to the ground to prevent the target from fleeing.

name: Spit Up
flavor_text: The power stored using the move Stockpile is released at once in an attack. The more power is stored, the greater the move’s power.

name: Spite
flavor_text: The user unleashes its grudge on the move last used by the target by cutting 4 PP from it.

name: Splash
flavor_text: The user just flops and splashes around to no effect at all...

name: Splintered Stormshards
flavor_text: After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Lycanroc, attacks the target with full force. This move negates the effect on the battlefield.

name: Splishy Splash
flavor_text: The user charges a huge wave with electricity and hits the opposing Pokémon with the wave. This may also leave the opposing Pokémon with paralysis.

name: Spore
flavor_text: The user scatters bursts of spores that induce sleep.

name: Spotlight
flavor_text: The user shines a spotlight on the target so that only the target will be attacked during the turn.

name: Springtide Storm
flavor_text: The user attacks by wrapping opposing Pokémon in fierce winds brimming with love and hate. This may also lower their Attack stats.

name: Stealth Rock
flavor_text: The user lays a trap of levitating stones around the opposing team. The trap damages opposing Pokémon that switch into battle.

name: Steam Eruption
flavor_text: The user immerses the target in superheated steam. This may also leave the target with a burn.

name: Steamroller
flavor_text: The user crushes its target by rolling over the target with its rolled-up body. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Steel Beam
flavor_text: The user fires a beam of steel that it collected from its entire body. This also damages the user.

name: Steel Roller
flavor_text: The user attacks while destroying the terrain. This move fails if the ground hasn’t turned into a terrain.

name: Steel Wing
flavor_text: The target is hit with wings of steel. This may also boost the user’s Defense stat.

name: Sticky Web
flavor_text: The user weaves a sticky net around the opposing team, which lowers their Speed stats upon switching into battle.

name: Stockpile
flavor_text: The user stores power and boosts its Defense and Sp. Def stats. This move can be used up to three times.

name: Stoked Sparksurfer
flavor_text: After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Alolan Raichu, attacks the target with full force. This move leaves the target with paralysis.

name: Stomp
flavor_text: The user attacks by stomping on the target with a big foot. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Stomping Tantrum
flavor_text: Driven by frustration, the user attacks the target. This move’s power is doubled if the user’s previous move failed.

name: Stone Axe
flavor_text: The user swings its stone axes at the target, aiming to land a critical hit. Stone splinters left behind by this attack float around the target.

name: Stone Edge
flavor_text: The user stabs the target with sharpened stones. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

name: Stored Power
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with stored power. The more the user’s stats are boosted, the greater the move’s power.

name: Storm Throw
flavor_text: The user attacks by striking the target with a fierce blow. This move always lands a critical hit.

name: Strange Steam
flavor_text: The user attacks the target by emitting steam. This may also confuse the target.

name: Strength
flavor_text: The target is slugged with a punch thrown at maximum power.

name: Strength Sap
flavor_text: The user restores its own HP by the same amount as the target’s Attack stat. It then lowers the target’s Attack stat.

name: String Shot
flavor_text: The user blows silk from its mouth that binds opposing Pokémon and harshly lowers their Speed stats.

name: Struggle
flavor_text: This attack is used in desperation only if the user has no remaining PP. It also damages the user a little.

name: Struggle Bug
flavor_text: The user attacks by struggling against opposing Pokémon. This also lowers their Sp. Atk stats.

name: Stuff Cheeks
flavor_text: The user eats its held Berry, then sharply boosts its Defense stat.

name: Stun Spore
flavor_text: The user scatters a cloud of numbing powder that paralyzes the target.

name: Submission
flavor_text: The user grabs the target and recklessly dives for the ground. This also damages the user a little.

name: Substitute
flavor_text: The user creates a substitute for itself using some of its own HP. The substitute serves as the user’s decoy.

name: Sucker Punch
flavor_text: This move enables the user to attack first. This move fails if the target is not readying an attack.

name: Sunny Day
flavor_text: The user intensifies the sun for five turns, powering up Fire-type attacks. The sunlight also lowers the power of Water-type attacks.

name: Sunsteel Strike
flavor_text: The user slams into the target with the force of a meteor. This move can be used on the target regardless of its Ability.

name: Super Fang
flavor_text: The user chomps hard on the target with its sharp front fangs. This cuts the target’s HP in half.

name: Superpower
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with great power. This also lowers the user’s Attack and Defense stats.

name: Supersonic
flavor_text: The user generates odd sound waves from its body that confuse the target.

name: Surf
flavor_text: The user attacks everything around it by swamping its surroundings with a giant wave.

name: Surging Strikes
flavor_text: The user, having mastered the Water style, strikes the target with a flowing motion three times in a row. This move always lands a critical hit.

name: Swagger
flavor_text: The user enrages and confuses the target. However, this also sharply boosts the target’s Attack stat.

name: Swallow
flavor_text: The power stored using the move Stockpile is absorbed by the user to restore its own HP. The more power is stored, the more HP is restored.

name: Sweet Kiss
flavor_text: The user kisses the target with a sweet, angelic cuteness that causes confusion.

name: Sweet Scent
flavor_text: The user releases a scent that harshly lowers opposing Pokémon’s evasiveness.

name: Swift
flavor_text: Star-shaped rays are shot at opposing Pokémon. This attack never misses.

name: Switcheroo
flavor_text: The user trades held items with the target faster than the eye can follow.

name: Swords Dance
flavor_text: A frenetic dance to uplift the fighting spirit. This sharply boosts the user’s Attack stat.

name: Synchronoise
flavor_text: Using an odd shock wave, the user inflicts damage on any Pokémon of the same type in the area around it.

name: Synthesis
flavor_text: The user restores its own HP. The amount of HP regained varies with the weather.

name: Syrup Bomb
flavor_text: The user sets off an explosion of sticky candy syrup, which coats the target and causes the target's Speed stat to drop each turn for three turns.

name: Tackle
flavor_text: A physical attack in which the user charges and slams into the target with its whole body.

name: Tail Glow
flavor_text: The user stares at flashing lights to focus its mind, drastically raising its Sp. Atk stat.

name: Tail Slap
flavor_text: The user attacks by striking the target with its hard tail. This move hits two to five times in a row.

name: Tail Whip
flavor_text: The user wags its tail cutely, making opposing Pokémon less wary. This lowers their Defense stats.

name: Tailwind
flavor_text: The user whips up a turbulent whirlwind that boosts the Speed stats of itself and its allies for four turns.

name: Take Down
flavor_text: A reckless full-body charge attack for slamming into the target. This also damages the user a little.

name: Take Heart
flavor_text: The user lifts its spirits, curing its own status conditions and boosting its Sp. Atk and Sp. Def stats.

name: Tar Shot
flavor_text: The user pours sticky tar over the target, lowering the target’s Speed stat. The target becomes weaker to Fire-type moves.

name: Taunt
flavor_text: The target is taunted into a rage that allows it to use only attack moves for three turns.

name: Tearful Look
flavor_text: The user gets teary-eyed to make the target lose its combative spirit. This lowers the target’s Attack and Sp. Atk stats.

name: Teatime
flavor_text: The user has teatime with all the Pokémon currently in the battle. Each Pokémon eats its held Berry.

name: Techno Blast
flavor_text: The user attacks by firing a beam of light at the target. This move’s type changes depending on the kind of drive held by the user.

name: Teeter Dance
flavor_text: The user performs a wobbly dance that confuses every Pokémon around it.

name: Telekinesis
flavor_text: The user makes the target float with its psychic power. The target is easier to hit for three turns.

name: Teleport
flavor_text: The user switches places with a party Pokémon in waiting, if any. If a wild Pokémon uses this move, it flees.

name: Tera Blast
flavor_text: If the user has Terastallized, it unleashes energy of its Tera Type. This move inflicts damage using the Attack or Sp. Atk stat—whichever is higher for the user.

name: Terrain Pulse
flavor_text: The user utilizes the energy of the terrain to attack. This move’s type and power change depending on the terrain at the time the move is used.

name: Thief
flavor_text: The user attacks and steals the target’s held item simultaneously. The user can’t steal anything if it already holds an item.

name: Thousand Arrows
flavor_text: This move can hit opposing Pokémon that are in the air. Those Pokémon will be knocked down to the ground.

name: Thousand Waves
flavor_text: The user attacks with a wave that crawls along the ground. Those it hits can’t flee from battle.

name: Thrash
flavor_text: The user rampages and attacks for two to three turns. The user then becomes confused.

name: Throat Chop
flavor_text: The user attacks the target’s throat, and the resultant suffering prevents the target from using sound-based moves for two turns.

name: Thunder
flavor_text: A wicked thunderbolt is dropped on the target to inflict damage. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

name: Thunder Cage
flavor_text: The user traps the target inside a cage of sparking electricity that inflicts damage for four to five turns.

name: Thunder Fang
flavor_text: The user bites with electrified fangs. This may also make the target flinch or leave it with paralysis.

name: Thunder Punch
flavor_text: The target is attacked with an electrified punch. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

name: Thunder Shock
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with a jolt of electricity. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

name: Thunder Wave
flavor_text: The user launches a weak jolt of electricity that paralyzes the target.

name: Thunderbolt
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with a strong electric blast. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

name: Thunderous Kick
flavor_text: The user overwhelms the target with lightning-like movement before delivering a kick. This also lowers the target’s Defense stat.

name: Tickle
flavor_text: The user tickles the target into laughing, lowering its Attack and Defense stats.

name: Tidy Up
flavor_text: The user tidies up and removes the effects of Spikes, Stealth Rock, Sticky Web, Toxic Spikes, and Substitute. This also boosts the user’s Attack and Speed stats.

name: Topsy-Turvy
flavor_text: All stat changes affecting the target turn topsy-turvy and become the opposite of what they were.

name: Torch Song
flavor_text: The user blows out raging flames as if singing a song, scorching the target. This also boosts the user’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Torment
flavor_text: The user torments and enrages the target, making it incapable of using the same move twice in a row.

name: Toxic
flavor_text: A move that leaves the target badly poisoned. Its poison damage worsens every turn.

name: Toxic Spikes
flavor_text: The user lays a trap of poison spikes at the feet of the opposing team. The spikes will poison opposing Pokémon that switch into battle.

name: Toxic Thread
flavor_text: The user shoots poisonous threads to poison the target and lower the target’s Speed stat.

name: Trailblaze
flavor_text: The user attacks suddenly as if leaping out from tall grass. The user’s nimble footwork boosts its Speed stat.

name: Transform
flavor_text: The user transforms into a copy of the target, right down to having the same move set.

name: Tri Attack
flavor_text: The user strikes with a simultaneous three-beam attack. This may also burn, freeze, or paralyze the target.

name: Trick
flavor_text: The user catches the target off guard and swaps the target’s held item with its own.

name: Trick Room
flavor_text: The user creates a bizarre area in which slower Pokémon get to move first for five turns.

name: Trick-or-Treat
flavor_text: The user takes the target trick-or-treating. This adds Ghost type to the target’s type.

name: Triple Arrows
flavor_text: The user kicks, then fires three arrows. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit and may also lower the target’s Defense stat or make it flinch.

name: Triple Axel
flavor_text: A consecutive three-kick attack that becomes more powerful with each successful hit.

name: Triple Dive
flavor_text: The user performs a perfectly timed triple dive, hitting the target with splashes of water three times in a row.

name: Triple Kick
flavor_text: A consecutive three-kick attack that becomes more powerful with each successful hit.

name: Trop Kick
flavor_text: The user lands an intense kick of tropical origins on the target. This also lowers the target’s Attack stat.

name: Trump Card
flavor_text: The fewer PP this move has, the greater its power.

name: Twin Beam
flavor_text: The user shoots mystical beams from its eyes to inflict damage. The target is hit twice in a row.

name: Twineedle
flavor_text: The user damages the target twice in succession by jabbing it with two spikes. This may also poison the target.

name: Twister
flavor_text: The user whips up a vicious tornado to tear at opposing Pokémon. This may also make them flinch.

name: U-turn
flavor_text: After making its attack, the user rushes back to switch places with a party Pokémon in waiting.

name: Uproar
flavor_text: The user attacks in an uproar for three turns. During that time, no Pokémon can fall asleep.

name: V-create
flavor_text: The user emits a hot flame from its forehead and hurls itself at the target to inflict damage. This also lowers the user’s Defense, Sp. Def, and Speed stats.

name: Vacuum Wave
flavor_text: The user whirls its fists to send a wave of pure vacuum at the target. This move always goes first.

name: Veevee Volley
flavor_text: The more Eevee loves its Trainer, the greater the move’s power. It never misses.

name: Venom Drench
flavor_text: Opposing Pokémon are drenched in an odd poisonous liquid. This lowers the Attack, Sp. Atk, and Speed stats of a poisoned target.

name: Venoshock
flavor_text: The user drenches the target in a special poisonous liquid. This move’s power is doubled if the target is poisoned.

name: Victory Dance
flavor_text: The user performs an intense dance to usher in victory, boosting its Attack, Defense, and Speed stats.

name: Vine Whip
flavor_text: The target is struck with slender, whiplike vines to inflict damage.

name: Vise Grip
flavor_text: The target is gripped and squeezed from both sides to inflict damage.

name: Vital Throw
flavor_text: The user attacks last. In return, this throw move never misses.

name: Volt Switch
flavor_text: After making its attack, the user rushes back to switch places with a party Pokémon in waiting.

name: Volt Tackle
flavor_text: The user electrifies itself and charges the target to inflict damage. This also damages the user quite a lot and may leave the target with paralysis.

name: Wake-Up Slap
flavor_text: This attack inflicts big damage on a sleeping target. This also wakes the target up, however.

name: Water Gun
flavor_text: The target is blasted with a forceful shot of water.

name: Water Pledge
flavor_text: A column of water hits the target. When used with its fire counterpart, this move’s power is boosted and a rainbow appears.

name: Water Pulse
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with a pulsing blast of water. This may also confuse the target.

name: Water Shuriken
flavor_text: The user hits the target with throwing stars two to five times in a row. This move always goes first.

name: Water Sport
flavor_text: The user soaks the battlefield with water. This weakens Fire-type moves for five turns.

name: Water Spout
flavor_text: The user spouts water to damage opposing Pokémon. The lower the user’s HP, the lower the move’s power.

name: Waterfall
flavor_text: The user charges at the target and may make it flinch.

name: Wave Crash
flavor_text: The user shrouds itself in water and slams into the target with its whole body to inflict damage. This also damages the user quite a lot.

name: Weather Ball
flavor_text: This move’s type and power change depending on the weather at the time the move is used.

name: Whirlpool
flavor_text: The user traps the target inside a violent, swirling whirlpool that inflicts damage for four to five turns.

name: Whirlwind
flavor_text: The target is blown away, and a different Pokémon is dragged out. In the wild, this ends a battle against a single Pokémon.

name: Wicked Blow
flavor_text: The user, having mastered the Dark style, strikes the target with a fierce blow. This move always lands a critical hit.

name: Wide Guard
flavor_text: The user and its allies are protected from wide-ranging attacks for one turn.

name: Wild Charge
flavor_text: The user shrouds itself in electricity and smashes into the target. This also damages the user a little.

name: Wildbolt Storm
flavor_text: The user summons a thunderous tempest and savagely attacks with lightning and wind. This may also leave opposing Pokémon with paralysis.

name: Will-O-Wisp
flavor_text: The user shoots a sinister flame at the target to inflict a burn.

name: Wing Attack
flavor_text: The target is struck with large, imposing wings spread wide to inflict damage.

name: Wish
flavor_text: One turn after this move is used, the user’s or its replacement’s HP is restored by up to half the user’s max HP.

name: Withdraw
flavor_text: The user withdraws its body into its hard shell, boosting its Defense stat.

name: Wonder Room
flavor_text: The user creates a bizarre area in which Pokémon’s Defense and Sp. Def stats are swapped for five turns.

name: Wood Hammer
flavor_text: The user slams its rugged body into the target to attack. This also damages the user quite a lot.

name: Work Up
flavor_text: The user is roused, and its Attack and Sp. Atk stats are boosted.

name: Worry Seed
flavor_text: A seed that causes worry is planted on the target. It prevents sleep by making the target’s Ability Insomnia.

name: Wrap
flavor_text: A long body, vines, or the like are used to wrap and squeeze the target for four to five turns.

name: Wring Out
flavor_text: The user powerfully wrings the target. The more HP the target has, the greater the move’s power.

name: X-Scissor
flavor_text: The user slashes at the target by crossing its scythes, claws, or the like as if they were a pair of scissors.

name: Yawn
flavor_text: The user lets loose a huge yawn that lulls the target into falling asleep on the next turn.

name: Zap Cannon
flavor_text: The user attacks by firing an electric blast like a cannon. This also leaves the target with paralysis.

name: Zen Headbutt
flavor_text: The user focuses its willpower to its head and attacks the target. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Zing Zap
flavor_text: The user crashes into the target, delivering a powerful electric shock. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Zippy Zap
flavor_text: The user attacks the target with bursts of electricity at high speed. This move always goes first and results in a critical hit.
